data.title: What are some interesting facts about the Siberian city of Yekaterinburg?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 2): 1. History: Yekaterinburg was founded in 1723 and named after Peter the Great's wife, Catherine I. It was an important industrial center during the Soviet era and was the site of several key events in Russian history, including the execution of the Romanov family in 1918.
